Monique Duval Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories The Hawks have arrested one of three men suspected to be responsible for killing a police officer in Philippi East on Tuesday 22 November.According to a statement by Hawks spokesperson Captain Lloyd Ramovha, the officers had just finished serving a protection order at one address when they were approached with a similar complaint within the vicinity. He says on their way to assist, they were suddenly allegedly shot at in Acacia Street after 20:00, by about three armed man, who subsequently robbed them of their firearms before they fled the scene. Ramovha says the trio killed one police officer while wounding her colleague.This morning (23 November), the Hawks swooped in on a 19-year-old man and arrested him for murder, attempted murder and robbery with aggravating circumstances. He is expected to appear in the Athlone&rsquo;s Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Friday.Meanwhile the Hawks are now on the hunt for the remaining suspects and anyone with information is asked to call 08600 1011 or send an SMS to 32211. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.